Paper: hep-th/0102006

Date: 2001-02-02

Title: Supersymmetry and Strongly Coupled Gauge Theories

Authors: Philip C. Argyres

Comments: 8 pages, 2 figures

Journal-ref: Nucl.Phys.Proc.Suppl. 101 (2001) 175-182

I briefly review how supersymmetry helps in the extraction of exactnonperturbative information from field theories, and then discuss some openproblems in strongly coupled gauge theories. (Talk given at ``30 Years ofSupersymmetry'' symposium in Minneapolis, Minnesota on October 15, 2000.)